Aloo posto is a popular Bengali dish – potatoes cooked in poppy seed paste, served with pooris or plain boiled rice. This delicately flavored curry gets its spice kick from two other trademark Bengali ingredients – mustard oil and panch phoron.

It's basically a dry vegetable dish that has various versions like Alu Chorchori which is made with Potatoes, Alu-Foolgobhi Chorchori which is a dry dish with Potatoes and Cauliflower, Begun Chorchori is made with Brinjal as the main ingredient and so on.
Chana Dal is a traditional Bengali dish prepared from Chana Dal (Bengal Gram Lentil), ghee, coconut, and other spices. It is sweet and savory and is best paired with Luchi or Steamed Rice.

menuDetails.dishName: KUMROR CHOKKA (BENGALI STYLE POTATO & PUMPKIN SABZI)
menuDetails.dishDescription: The Kumror Chokka Recipe is a classic Bengali dish which is packed with flavours from panch phoran masala and spices and cooked in mustard oil. Kumror means pumpkin in bengali and is a very commonly used vegetable in the Bengali Cuisine. Pumpkin is a very nutritious vegetable, that is low in calories, rich in Vitamin A, potassium, manganese and lots of other essential minerals.
A lovely subzi recipe from West Bengal. Big cubes of potatoes are deep-fried and mixed with marinated soya chunks.
Chanar Dalna is a typical niramish (vegetarian) Bengali dish where homemade paneer balls or koftas are fried and cooked in a lightly spiced, subtly sweet gravy with potatoes.

Doi begun is a classic Bengali recipe which is immensely popular among Bengalis.subtle fried eggplant pieces are dunked in mildly spicy sweet and tangy yogurt-based gravy. It is mostly relished with plain rice or flat breads like roti, parotta or luchi.

Macher Jhol is one of the most popular dishes and is an important part of Bengali cuisine. Prepared using minimal spices, fish, and vegetables like potato and eggplant, Macher Jhol is essentially a spicy fish stew that is enjoyed best with hot steaming rice.

The word kosha is similar in meaning to bhuna, which involves slowly cooking a gravy over low flame for a very long time to get a rich, dark-brown gravy and melt-in-the-mouth mutton pieces. Mutton kosha (or kosha mangsho) can be served with porota or polao. It tastes great even with plain rice.

This chicken curry recipe yields tender chicken pieces in a hot, flavourful, stew-like jhol (curry). The defining characteristic of the Bengali-style chicken curry is the presence of potatoes, which, when cooked in the curry, become soft and succulent, full of all the juicy goodness of the curry. This recipe has two parts: the first involves marinating the chicken, and the second, preparing the curry.

Bengali Doi Murgi or Bengali Chicken Curry is a delicious Bengali style chicken curry where chicken is cooked in a spicy yogurt sauce. ... An aromatic dish made using chicken, onions, and a lot of yogurt flavored with a medley of spices that renders this chicken curry a beautiful aroma and a unique taste.
It has few ingredients and they play a crucial role.The strong flavor of mustard and the hotness of green chilies makes the dish delicious and unique from other fish curries.
This ‘pulao’ is a little sweet as  Bengalis prefer ‘pulao’ to be a little sweet.

Basanti pulao is a traditional Bengali dish prepared during festivals and special occasions. This aromatic and bright yellow coloured rice is flavoured with whole spices. Raisins and cashews add a royal touch to this dish.
This biryani uses ground biryani masala powder.This is mildly spiced and light.
Kadhi is a traditional Gujarati preparation of a wonderful sweet and spicy curd mixture thickened with besan.
Gujarati style tempered rice or seasoned rice. Mix the rice with spice powders and then temper them with mustard and cumin seeds.
Oondiyu is a preparation of vegetables and fenugreek muthaias cooked in an aromatic blend of spices.
Bardoli Ki Khichdi Recipe is a spicy khichdi recipe from the region on Bardoli in Gujarat. A combination of vegetables, rice and toor dal, this dish is packed with nutrients.
Thepla is a flatbread made of whole wheat flour,oil and spice powders like turmeric,red chilli powder.

Gujarati dal recipe is a unique tasting soupy lentil dish that has two contrasting flavors – sweet and sour. A bit of sweet and some sourness in any dish tastes too good and so does in this Gujarati dal.
Kala Chana or Black Chana is a very good source of vegetarian protein. It can be cooked in a variety of forms like chaat, curries, or ghugni.
Fried elephant foot yam, is a crispy spiced veggie dish made with simple, wholesome ingredients. It’s delicious for a snack or side, and pairs great with any number of main courses.
An absolutely delectable dish which is packed flavours from green chillies, the stewed tomatoes and the crunchy sev. Serve it along with Thepla oe Bhakri for lunch or dinner.

Kobi batata Nu Shaak is traditional Gujarati recipe which is prepared as a everyday shaak recipe in Gujarati households. This recipe consists of cabbage and potatoes cooked in traditional Gujarati spices.
This nutritious vegetable panchmel khichdi is made of 4 dals and rice pressure cooked with a generous helping of crunchy vegetables,tomatoes and spice powders.

Made with rice,yellow moong dal and curds,along with everyday spices,the Dahiwali Moong dal khichdi has the lingering flavour of curds and as inherent simplicity and lightness that make it very appealing.
Gujarati Khari Bhat or masala bhat is a spicy colourful pulao which is really simple to make.adding curry leaves and peanuts which sounded so good.
Khichdi is a simple, classic Indian dish made with rice and yellow mung lentils. It is actually a very healthy.
Chungdi malai is one of the most coveted dishes of Puri,Coconut milk and shrimp are natural dancing partners
Ghanta in oriya means 'mixed' and each specific ghanta has a typical set of vegetables to be added. Macha ghanta has the additional fish pieces in it.

Dalma is a Chickpea Dal Cooked With Vegetables and Raw Papaya, a delicacy from the state of Orissa. It can be made using toor (arhar) dal, and an assortment of vegetables typically raw banana, eggplant, green papaya and pumpkins, simmered in a special spice blend.
Kanika is a mildly sweet fragrant rice flavored with some spices and ghee (the clarified butter) loaded with cashew nuts and raisins and is colored with the turmeric.
Pilaf is a rice dish,or  a wheat dish, whose recipe usually involves cooking in stock or broth, adding spices, and other ingredients such as vegetables or meat
Potatoes, raw papaya and brinjals cooked in milk, chillies and masalas. Santula is a very popular vegetable dish of Orrisa.
This dish is a traditional Odiya Mushroom dish that shows how tempting it turns out with the touch of Mustard.
Aloo potala rasa is a spicy curry prepared with potatoes and pointed gourd. It is one of the popular curries from the state of Odisha.
Besara is a traditional odia dish which made out with lots of selected vegetables, using mustard paste and little jaggery.

Barali vangi is an authentic spicy curry recipe made with purple eggplant and blend of stuffed spices. it is one of the popular curries from the marathi cuisine, loaded with the warmth of goda masala.
Pitla is a traditional Maharashtrian curry made with besan (gram flour) and onions. A spicy base of ginger-garlic-green-chillies and onions is cooked with gram flour and water until thick.
It gets its distinct taste from being a gentle blend of spicy, a little sweet and a little tangy flavours.

It’s a very comforting dish and is usually served with plain white rice. The classic combination of the two – the Varan (dal) and Bhaat (rice) is usually said together and is considered one word – Varan Bhaat.
Kadhi is a popular North Indian dish, made with besan and dahi as main ingredients along with various spices and pakodas dipped in it.
Pandhra rassa is chicken or mutton broth cooked with coconut. It is a famous recipe from Kolhapur.
Tambada means Red and Rassa means Stews/Curry.
Kolhapuri Chicken is a chicken curry that is full of the rich, varied, spicy kolhapuri flavors
It is a mixture of spices like goda masala and vegetables. it is generally served for breakfast or lunch and is often termed as tiffin box recipe or lunch box recipe.
Varan bhaat would read as lentil-rice where varan stands for “lentil curry or stew or dal” and bhaat means “steamed rice”.
It is made with white rice cooked in a base of coconut milk and combined with shredded coconut meat, water, salt, raisins (optional), and sugar.
Vangi bath is a flavorful dish made with brinjals,spice powder,spices and herbs.
Tendli stands for ivy gourd and bhaat stands for rice.Tendli and rice combination turns even heavenly.
This is a very popular spicy and flavourful curry from coastal region of Maharashtra.
This is a semi-dry gravy with masala
Dal Bati -a traditional dish from the state of Rajasthan in India. Hard wheat balls are baked and then eaten a spicy mix of lentils. It’s topped with lots of ghee which makes it extremely flavorful.
Gatta are gram flour (besan) roundels which are added to a curd based gravy.
Gatta curry is made with gram flour dumplings boiled in water,sliced and added in a spicy yoghurt curry.
Delicious mutton cooked in ginger garlic paste, yogurt, turmeric and more. It is meant to be fiery which is made with the combination of Kashmiri red chillies and other popular spices of Rajasthan.
Ker Sangri is a traditional,spicy sabzi made with thr ker berry and the sangri bean.
Very famous and superlicious pulao with very simple ingredients with very tender and soft-cooked meat.

Gatte ka pulao is spicy rice dish from Marwari cuisine of Rajasthan. This traditional Rajasthani rice recipe is made with chickpeas flour dumplings called gatta and rice cooked with a lot of aromatic spices.
Aloo matar is a mouth watering curry of potato and green peas that tastes delicious when served with phulka roti,chapati or paratha.
Dahi Aloo is a rich and creamy gravy delicacy from Rajasthan
creamy curry of soft succulent paneer and plenty of onions in a wonderful medley of spices, herbs and tomatoes.
Dal banjara is a delicious dal receipe made with chiklewali urad dal and chana dal.

It is usually made with a side dish to serve it along with phulka or rice. It is spicy and is specially made during the winter season. This kadhi has some delicious flavours which comes from the spicy masalas used in the dish.
A judicious mix of five vegetables- gavarfali,chawli,capsicum,cucumber and carrots.Tossed in aromatic spices,this dry vegetable preparation tastes fantastic when served with rotis and bhakris.
Marinate chicken in mango paste and ginger-garlic paste with spices.
It is a spicy chicken delicacy where the marinated chicken pieces are slow cooked with Indian spices.

Masala nachos are Indian version of nachos. It is prepared with wheat flour and some Indian spices, cut into the nachos shape and fried in Oil. It tastes delicious and very crispy. Masala nachos are great tea time snacks.
Kachoris are deep fried breads made with ground dal sauteed along with spices and filled into a cover of maida and baking powder.
Kachoris are deep fried breads made with ground dal sauteed along with spices and filled into a cover of maida and baking powder.
This is made with simple veggies like cabbage,carrots and capsicum.The filling is made by sauteing the veggies in a Chinese style on a high flame which lends that nice unique aroma.
Potato wedges make for a great appetizer or a snack.These are delicious,crisp,flavorful and spicy.
Masala Bhel is a low calorie snack that is addictive,tastes delicious and is flavored packed with indian masalas.
Kala chana chaat is a tangy and tasty snack made from black chickpeas. It is much similar to the green chana chaat
Tosted bun with a samosa-spiced veggie patty made from potatoes and peas,onion and tomato.
It is a deep fried chick pea balls,served with a tangy tahini paste(it's a mixture of tahini paste, lemon juice, garlic and water)
Misal Pav is a vibrant meal consisting of a spicy sprouted bean curry topped with crunchy Farsan, crisp red onions, and fresh cilantro that is served with lightly buttered Pav or dinner rolls.
It is basically a savory slider of fried mashed potato fritters stuffed in a dinner roll.
Choley patties are made from chickpea,potato and breadcrumbs.It is flavored with spices and shallow fried in a pan.It is crisp from outside and soft from inside
The combination of dried chickpeas, tahini, and olive oil results in a puree that's rich in vitamin E, antioxidants, calcium, iron, protein, fiber, vitamin A, and thiamine.
It is made with a fermented batter derived from rice, ground urad dal, and chickpea flour. Dhokla can be eaten for breakfast, as a main course, as a side dish, or as a snack.
This south indian stir-fry made with french beans,banana and coconut are wrapped

Stuffed Vegetable Kulcha is a soft and fluffy Indian leavened bread which is made stuffed with seasonal vegetables. It's also a delicious way to feed more vegetables to kids or use up leftover vegetables form the previous meal.
Contains mashed Batata(sweet potato) masala,spread butter and coriander chutney on bread slices,placed mashed batata.
bread slices are layered with a luscious mixture of potatoes and spinach puree flavored with ginger,garlic and green chillies.
Chickpeas curry with indian masala
Kathi roll has a stuffing of assorted veggies, cheese, meat, paneer, soya and a melange of spices
Flattened rice with potato,green chutney and masala with Tomato chutney
A healthy and tasty breakfast recipe or upma recipe made from the broken or cracked wheat. it is a popular and nutritional alternative to the traditional rava or sooji upma
Pongal is a popular south indian food made with rice and moong dal which is tempered with ghee,curry leaves,black pepper,ginger,cumin and hing.
Bisibele bathis a popular dish made with rice,lentils,mix veggeies and a special spice powder.
Khichdi using lentils,spices and quick cook veggies with broken wheat.
Khichdi using lentils,spices and quick cook veggies with red rice.
A popular south indian breakfast with ground urad dal.idli batter is fermented and steamed cook
Flattened rice is steamed cooked with onions,spices and herbs.
Sewaiyan upma is a popular south indian breakfast made with wheat vermicelli,spices,herbs and peanuts.
Upma is a flavorful south indian breakfast dish made from rava or cream of wheat.
It is a tempering south india dish prepared by adding lemon juice while stir frying steamed rice in spices.

Set dosa is a popular breakfast.A set of soft and thick spongy dosas are served together with coconut chutney and sagu. This is a basic set dosa recipe that can even be used to make dosas without oil on a nonstick tawa.
It is so delicious ans is devoid sauces,chutney or cheese with loads of creepy ingredients.
Indian spiced potatoes are seasoned with mustard seeds,turmeric and garlic.
It is a delicious dish of tapioca pearls(sago) made with potatoes,peanuts.
It is plain parathas are indian flatbread that the crisper and flakier version of pulkas.
Aloo paratha is a popular Indian breakfast of unleavened whole wheat savory and spiced potato stuffed flatbread.
It is precooked rice with lots of tomatoes and spices.

These breakfast quesadillas are stuffed with fluffy scrambled eggs, melt-in-your-mouth pinto beans, fresh herbs and gooey cheddar cheese, all of which contrasts so nicely with the crisp, golden exterior.
Uttappam are south indian breakfast pancakes made with lentils,rice,onions,herbs and spices.
Puliyogare is a tamarind rice made by tempering precooked rice with spicy tamarind paste.It is very flavorful and tastes.
Rava idli is a soft,pillowy savory cake made from rava or suji with vegetables.
Aloo rasedar is a spiced, thin potato curry made with tomatoes, ginger & spices. No onion no garlic recipe

Baingan Ka Salan is popular Hyderabadi curry recipe. It contains peanuts, dried coconut, sesame seeds, ginger, and garlic paste, basic Indian spices and, for sourness, either thick tamarind juice is used or curd/yogurt.
Turai is also known as ridge gourd and similar to zucchini. Turai is outer skin is bright green in color and inside white pulp and white seeds embedded within in a spongy flesh with peas.

Kala Chana is a mildly spiced black chickpeas curry made in the instant pot or a stovetop pressure cooker. This is a simple everyday Punjabi curry, made in a onion-tomato gravy with ginger and garlic.
Dum Aloo is a delicious recipe of baby potatoes cooked in a gravy or sauce. Baby potatoes curry spiced with fennel, ginger and whole spices.
It is delecious food prepared by using many vegetables,tomato,onion,spinach,cachew paste,greated cheese and spices.
This is a gravy like dish prepared with fresh green peas, onions, tomatoes and spices.
It is the most popular Sindhi dish had with chawal. It is made from gavarfali, potatoes, drumstick, bhindi, little besan and Indian spices.

It is a beautiful  medley of lightly roasted vegetables simmered in creamy spinach puree and spiced right with roasted Indian garam masala. This veg handi sabzi is very unique mix vegetable curry, slowly cooked over a slow flame for hours in creamy spinach gravy.
It is delecious dish using sya,potato and spices.
It is very spicy,healthy rich with masala and counted in shahi curry.
Suran ki Sabji or yam curry is a delicious, spicy and tangy Indian curry cooked in mustard onion tomato masala gravy. This curry pairs best with steamed rice, pooris or parathas.
Avial Recipe is a thick mixture of veggies, coconut, seasoned with coconut oil.
chilli paneer is a Indo chinese starter or appetizer made by tossing fried paneer in sweet sour and spicy chilli sauce.
It is a sweet, spicy& slightly sour crispy appetizer made with chicken, bell peppers, garlic, chilli sauce &soya sauce.
Cut paneer into bite-size cubes, heat oil in a shallow frying pan over medium heat, add the panner.
Chicken pieces cooked in onion tomato gravy creates an authentic Dhaba style chicken curry
Tari wala is a Punjabi dish, Chicken curry with whole spices, turmeric, ginger and coriander.
Matar paneer is one of the most popular paneer dishes made with green peas, Indian cheese, onions, tomatoes, spices and herbs.
Murgh Palak Gravy Recipe is a classic North Indian gravy made with marinated chicken, pureed spinach and whole spices.
Lehsuni Methi Paneer is a creamy and delicious restaurant style North Indian Curry Recipe.  Paneer is cooked with Kasuri Methi and Garlic creamy gravy.

Amritsari Dal recipe is an authentic winter food among the people of Punjab. The Dal is made with a blend of Black Urad Dal and Channa Dal which is cooked in a pressure cooker. Then the dal is tempered with onions, ginger, garlic and flavoured with authentic spices.

Rajma is kidney beans curry which is made by pressure cooking raw kidney beans which are soaked overnight.The pressure cooked beans are then cooked with onion, tomatoes, ginger-garlic and with spices like coriander, garam masala, chili powder.
Lobia Dal is a very popular North Indian dish and have a thick gravy of onion, garlic, tomatoes and spices.
Sambar is a South Indian staple dish that is served for all the meals including breakfast, lunch, and dinner. It is a stew of yellow lentils with vegetables and spices added to it.
Dal Palak is also one of the popular Indian lentil recipes as it combines the goodness of the pigeon pea lentils as well as spinach.

Ghar Ki Dal is a mixed dal fry made from four different varieties of lentils and is very much popular in our Indian cuisine. It is a protein-packed dish with the goodness of four different varieties of dal and extra nutrition.

Panchmel dal is a Rajasthani style Dal which is made by mixing five different varieties of lentils.The mix of five different types of lentils, which generally are hari moong dal, dhuli moong dal, chana dal, kali urad dal and masoor dal.

Dalma Recipe is a traditional and healthy dish from the Indian state of Odisha. Dalma is a combination of mixed vegetables and lentils tempered with panch phoran masala and garnished with coconut and coriander leaves.

Watana Korma is made from meat or vegetables braised with cream or yogurt, water or stock, and multiple spices to make a thick glaze or sauce. The dish is also often mixed with slow-cooked and yogurt-marinated meats.
Dal Miloni is one of the most popular lentil recipes from the North Indian Punjabi cuisine made with Whole Black Lentils and Kidney Beans.
Langar waali dal is a special lentil recipe prepared with three lentils cooked together and tempered with special spices.This is a no onion -no garlic recipe.
Pakwan is a deep fried, crisp bread made with all purpose flour. These fried breads have the flavor of carom seeds, cumin and crushed black pepper.
Tomato pappu is red lentils that is cooked until fall apart tender and simmered with a ginger, tomato and spice sauce.
It has a mild ginger flavor that can be enhanced according to taste and seasonal veggies used.
Lauki Chana Dal is a simple nutritious curry made with bottle gourd and bengal gram lentils. This is a North Indian or Punjabi style preparation for this curry made in a pressure cooker.
Punjabi Chana Masala or Chole Masala is an authentic North Indian style Chickpea Curry made with white chickpeas, freshly powdered spices, onions, tomatoes and herbs.
Gatta Curry is a delicacy of the Indian state of Rajasthan. In this curry chickpea flour dumplings are cooked in a spicy and tangy yogurt sauce.
